description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Medical Workforce Administrator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;24.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Medical Workforce team at Greater Manchester Mental Health (GMMH) NHS Foundation Trust. This is a fixed term appointment until 31&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;st&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; March, 2021.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Medical Workforce team is a small and friendly team dedicated to providing a broad range of Medical Workforce support to the medical staff across the organisation. The postholder will have the opportunity to gain experience across a broad range of Medical Workforce processes including medical locum bookings and rota planning. This range of duties means you will work in a role that offers both variety and plenty of opportunities for learning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post-holder will report into the Medical Workforce Co-ordinator and will be supported and developed on a day to day basis by the senior members of the team. Although the role is well supported, the ability to plan your workload and work autonomously will be expected.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience in Medical Workforce and the NHS would be an advantage but isn&#39;t essential, as long as you have experience in a similar working environment, as well as good administration and customer service skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Training in the role and in Medical Workforce matters will be provided to the successful applicant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to supporting our employees to achieve a good work life balance and as well as offering a supportive working environment, we are happy to consider flexible working applications. To assist us in considering possible flexible working arrangements please outline any preferred working patterns or part time working proposals in the Supporting Information section of your application form. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jo Kenyon&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Medical Workforce Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address joanne.kenyon@gmmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
